at can simply be wiped off or become brittle . However, the color is intense and hardly fades. So you can easily wash or rinse them without losing color brightness. They are also resistant to UV radiation and harmful environmental effects. This makes sublimation printing also suitable for outdoor use - for example, for printing on flags. In addition, the ink does not seal the fabric: properties such as breathability are preserved - ideal for sportswear and club jerseys. Sublimation printing is also a particularly environmentally friendly process as no adhesives or solvents are required.</span></p><h5 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu eBgidd pf-111_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-110_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Cons:</span></span></h5><p class="sc-eGPXGI dCeUID pf-105_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-104_">For sublimation printing, you need a special printer and sublimation ink. Therefore, the initial cost is higher compared to some other methods. The main disadvantage of this sublimation printing is that it is expensive. While dye-sublimation printers are suitable for both home and professional use, small home printers can cost around $300, while higher-end products can cost as much as $600. They can cost as much as $10,000 for mass-produced large printers.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu eBgidd pf-114_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-113_"><span style="font-weight: 700;">What Materials Can Be Sublimated?</span></span></h2><p class="sc-eGPXGI dCeUID pf-117_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-116_">If you are considering starting your own printing business and want to take advantage of sublimation printing, or if you want to start the process at home, it is important to know what materials are available to you. these are:<br>â€“ Polyester cotton textiles<br>â€“ Polymers<br>â€“ Polyester<br>- Ceramics<br>â€“ PVC<br>â€“ Polyester coated aluminium<br>â€“ Polymer coated metal<br>â€“ Polyester fabric<br>â€“ Polymer coated plastic<br>The best materials for sublimation printing in the above list are polyester or ceramic.<br><br>Is there any material that cannot be sublimated? 100% cotton material or other natural materials are not suitable for this printing method. This is because they do not have the pores needed to absorb ink. If you are working with these types of materials, perhaps digital printing is more suitable.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu eBgidd pf-120_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-119_"><span style="font-weight: 700;">What is needed for sublimation printing?</span></span></h2><p class="sc-eGPXGI dCeUID pf-123_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-122_">1.Sublimation Printer
